<TITLE> Nazrul's birth anniversary on Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 24 (bdnews24.com)  Kazi Nazrul Islam's 111th anniversary of birth is set to be observed due fervour on Tuesday. President Zillur Rahman will be inaugurating the ceremony to celebrate the national poet's birthday at 11.30am at the 'Nazrul Mancha' at Mymensingh's Trishal. Wreaths will be placed into the poet's grave. Bangla Academy, Shilpakala Academy, Nazrul Institute and a number of other organisations are also expected to host day-long programmes to mark the occasion. The president, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and opposition leader Khaleda Zia have issued special messages. Bangladesh Television and Radio and private TV channels will telecast programmes portraying the rebel poet's life and works. Kazi Nazrul Islam, the revolutionary poet and great lyricist of Bengal, was born on May 24, 1899 and died on August 29, 1976. Nazrul took the Bengali literary world by storm with his moving poetry. His chief works are: Agnibina, Sanchita, Dolan Chanpa, Chhayanaut. bdn
